{"ClientSettings":{"Pn":{"Cn":1,"St":0,"Qs":0,"Prod":"P"},"Sc":{"Cn":1,"St":0,"Qs":0,"Prod":"H"},"Qz":{"Cn":1,"St":0,"Qs":0,"Prod":"T"},"Ap":true,"Mute":true,"Lad":"2026-05-09T00:00:00Z","Iotd":0,"Gwb":0,"Tns":0,"Dft":null,"Mvs":0,"Flt":0,"Imp":1,"Tobn":0},"MediaContents":[{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Water is the architect of Krka National Park in Croatia, shaping emerald pools and layered waterfalls along the Krka River. Today's image highlights Skradinski Buk, the park's most famous waterfall system, where multiple streams spill over travertine terraces in a dense forest near the village of Lozovac.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.SkradinskiBuk_EN-CA8816657726_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.SkradinskiBuk_EN-CA8816657726_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"The architect of Krka","Title":"Skradinski Buk Waterfall in Krka National Park, Croatia","Copyright":"© Amazing Aerial Agency/Adobe Stock","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/43.805592,15.963964/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-CA&od=2&shading=flat&pp=43.805592,15.963964;S9;Skradinski Buk Waterfall, Krka National Park, Lozovac, Croatia&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260509_SkradinskiBuk\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Krka+National+Park+Croatia&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260509_0400\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260509_SkradinskiBuk"},"Ssd":"20260509","Name":"SkradinskiBuk","Market":"EN-CA","Hash":"8816657726","FullDateString":"May 9, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"It starts quietly—rows of tulips opening along the Rideau Canal as spring settles in. Then the story catches up. The Canadian Tulip Festival begins today, marking its 74th year, but its roots go back to wartime Europe. In 1945, after Canada helped liberate the Netherlands and hosted Princess Juliana during her exile, a gift of tulip bulbs arrived in Ottawa. That tradition didn't end; it returned each year, growing into today's festival.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.TulipFestOT_EN-CA8431484438_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.TulipFestOT_EN-CA8431484438_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"When Ottawa turns tulip","Title":"Tulips and cherry blossoms at the Rideau Canal, Ottawa, Ontario","Copyright":"© J Duquette/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"There are over 3,000 registered tulip varieties.","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260508_TulipFestOT\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Canadian+Tulip+Festival&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260508_0400\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260508_TulipFestOT"},"Ssd":"20260508","Name":"TulipFestOT","Market":"EN-CA","Hash":"8431484438","FullDateString":"May 8, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Stretching across the Sonoran Desert in southwestern Arizona, Kofa National Wildlife Refuge is a land of sharp peaks, wide skies and surprising life. The refuge was established in 1939 to protect desert bighorn sheep, whose sure-footed silhouettes still define the rugged landscape.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.Kofa_EN-CA1760783023_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.Kofa_EN-CA1760783023_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Desert, drawn wide","Title":"Kofa National Wildlife Refuge, Arizona, United States","Copyright":"© Denis Tangney Jr/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/33.237633,-114.011215/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-CA&od=2&shading=flat&pp=33.237633,-114.011215;S9;Kofa National Wildlife Refuge, Arizona, United States&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260507_Kofa\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Kofa+National+Wildlife+Refuge&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260507_0400\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260507_Kofa"},"Ssd":"20260507","Name":"Kofa","Market":"EN-CA","Hash":"1760783023","FullDateString":"May 7, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Located on the eastern Balkan Peninsula, Bulgaria sits at the crossroads of Europe and Asia, where ancient cultures, fertile landscapes and shifting climates converge.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.BulgariaPlains_EN-CA6379116198_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.BulgariaPlains_EN-CA6379116198_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Plains under pressure","Title":"Thunderstorm above the plains, Bulgaria","Copyright":"© Revolu7ion93/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/42.75,25.5/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-CA&od=2&shading=flat&pp=42.75,25.5;S9;Bulgaria&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260506_BulgariaPlains\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Bulgaria&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260506_0400\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260506_BulgariaPlains"},"Ssd":"20260506","Name":"BulgariaPlains","Market":"EN-CA","Hash":"6379116198","FullDateString":"May 6, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Not one to hurry, a bull moose moves with steady purpose—and for good reason. As part of the North American moose population native to Canada, these animals are well adapted to long winters and short growing seasons. Their diet shifts with availability: in summer, they browse fresh leaves, shrubs and aquatic plants; in winter, they rely more on woody material like twigs and bark.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.BullQuebec_EN-CA5955231847_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.BullQuebec_EN-CA5955231847_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"In step with the forest","Title":"A majestic bull moose foraging through the green undergrowth, Quebec","Copyright":"© pchoui/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"Moose are excellent swimmers and are known to wade into water to eat aquatic plants.","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260505_BullQuebec\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Moose+animal&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260505_0400\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260505_BullQuebec"},"Ssd":"20260505","Name":"BullQuebec","Market":"EN-CA","Hash":"5955231847","FullDateString":"May 5, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"May the 4th be with you! On Star Wars Day, reality cosplays as science fiction and dares you to tell the difference. Our image takes us to Ksar Ouled Soltane in Tunisia's Tataouine district, where stacked clay granaries rise like sand‑coloured fortresses. Dating back to the 15th century, this storehouse complex was built by Berber communities to protect harvests from heat, theft and time. Function first. Beauty as a side effect.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.KsarOuledSoltane_EN-CA5863757495_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.KsarOuledSoltane_EN-CA5863757495_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Sci‑fi, Earth‑made","Title":"Ksar Ouled Soltane, Tataouine district in southern Tunisia","Copyright":"© Dark_Eni/Getty Images Plus","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/32.793106,10.518624/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-CA&od=2&shading=flat&pp=32.793106,10.518624;S9;Ksar Ouled Soltane, Tataouine, Tunisia&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260504_KsarOuledSoltane\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Star+Wars+Day&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260504_0400\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260504_KsarOuledSoltane"},"Ssd":"20260504","Name":"KsarOuledSoltane","Market":"EN-CA","Hash":"5863757495","FullDateString":"May 4, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"High above the savannah in Kenya's Masai Mara, a leopard curls up on a tree branch, napping as the grasslands glow at sunset. On International Leopard Day, observed on May 3, we celebrate one of the world's most adaptable big cats. Leopards roam across Africa and parts of Asia, thriving in habitats that range from forests and mountains to open savannahs. Their spotted coats are unique to each individual, like fingerprints, and their powerful climbing skills allow them to stash prey high in trees, out of reach of scavengers.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.MasaiLeopard_EN-CA1789008589_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.MasaiLeopard_EN-CA1789008589_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Savannah afterglow","Title":"Leopard sleeping in a tree in the savannah, Masai Mara National Reserve, Kenya","Copyright":"© Klein & Hubert/Nature Picture Library","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"Leopards have lost about 75% of their historical distribution and are classified as 'vulnerable' by the IUCN.","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260503_MasaiLeopard\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=International+Leopard+Day&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260503_0400\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260503_MasaiLeopard"},"Ssd":"20260503","Name":"MasaiLeopard","Market":"EN-CA","Hash":"1789008589","FullDateString":"May 3, 2026"}],"PreloadMediaContents":[{"ImageContent":{"Description":"What do you call a place where the rocks do the climbing, and humans try to keep up? Welcome to Smith Rock State Park in Oregon, where cliffs rise fast, and excuses fall faster. It sits inside the 40-kilometre-long Crooked River Caldera, shaped by multiple volcanic eruptions. Its welded tuff cliffs are made from compressed volcanic ash that cooled under pressure. The Crooked River carved the canyon, while formations like the Spire rise up to 180 metres.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.SmithRockPark_EN-CA4269417858_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.SmithRockPark_EN-CA4269417858_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Rock bottom? Not here","Title":"Smith Rock State Park, Oregon, United States","Copyright":"© Alex Ratson/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/44.368233,-121.14061/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-CA&od=2&shading=flat&pp=44.368233,-121.14061;S9;Smith Rock State Park, Oregon, United States&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260516_SmithRockPark\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Smith+Rock+State+Park&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260516_0400\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260516_SmithRockPark"},"Ssd":"20260516","Name":"SmithRockPark","Market":"EN-CA","Hash":"4269417858","FullDateString":"May 16, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Brains, brawn and a serious case of going deep—the sperm whale isn't here for surface-level living. This Endangered Species Day, meet a giant that thinks big and dives deeper.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.EndangeredWhales_EN-CA3958400554_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.EndangeredWhales_EN-CA3958400554_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Whale you save me?","Title":"A family of sperm whales, Indian Ocean","Copyright":"© Tony Wu/Nature Picture Library","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"The term cachalot is often used for sperm whales, derived from an archaic French term meaning 'big teeth.'","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260515_EndangeredWhales\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Endangered+Species+Day&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260515_0400\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260515_EndangeredWhales"},"Ssd":"20260515","Name":"EndangeredWhales","Market":"EN-CA","Hash":"3958400554","FullDateString":"May 15, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Perched on a tufa ridge in southern Tuscany, Italy, Pitigliano is a small town with a big personality. Its roots stretch back to Etruscan times, and the winding streets still echo the past, from medieval fortifications to Renaissance palaces. Walking through its narrow alleys, you can feel centuries of life carved into the stone, while small piazzas invite pauses for coffee or gelato. This enduring treasure is often called 'Little Jerusalem' for its historic Jewish quarter, where a synagogue and historic cemetery tell stories of a once-thriving community.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.Pitigliano_EN-CA9857257534_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.Pitigliano_EN-CA9857257534_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"A journey through time","Title":"Medieval town of Pitigliano, Tuscany, Italy","Copyright":"© bluejayphoto/Getty Images Plus","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/42.636668,11.669293/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-CA&od=2&shading=flat&pp=42.636668,11.669293;S9;Pitigliano, Tuscany, Italy&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260514_Pitigliano\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Pitigliano+Tuscany&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260514_0400\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260514_Pitigliano"},"Ssd":"20260514","Name":"Pitigliano","Market":"EN-CA","Hash":"9857257534","FullDateString":"May 14, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"In today's image, the granite arches of the Alabama Hills frame the Milky Way over a rugged landscape in California's eastern Sierra Nevada. Famous for its rounded boulders and weathered rock formations, this area formed when molten rock cooled deep underground around 100 million years ago. Water and wind gradually shaped the stone into the smooth shapes seen today. Visitors can explore the natural arches, hike among the rocks, capture photographs of the unique landscape, ride horses or mountain bikes and enjoy seasonal displays of wildflowers.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.AlabamaHills_EN-CA2745537583_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.AlabamaHills_EN-CA2745537583_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Rock on, Milky Way!","Title":"Arch and Milky Way, Alabama Hills, Sierra Nevada, California, United States","Copyright":"© Tim Fitzharris/Minden Pictures","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/36.981191,-118.081229/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-CA&od=2&shading=flat&pp=36.981191,-118.081229;S9;Alabama Hills, Sierra Nevada, California, USA&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260513_AlabamaHills\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Alabama+Hills&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260513_0400\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260513_AlabamaHills"},"Ssd":"20260513","Name":"AlabamaHills","Market":"EN-CA","Hash":"2745537583","FullDateString":"May 13, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Along the rocky coasts of the North Atlantic, Atlantic puffins make their homes in burrows and cliffside crevices. These seabirds, with their black‑and‑white plumage and colourful beaks, are classified by the IUCN as vulnerable, as overfishing and changing ocean conditions reduce the availability of their prey. Each spring, they return to breed, laying a single egg in carefully dug burrows. Remarkable swimmers, they use their wings to 'fly' underwater when hunting small fish such as herring and sand eels.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.Fratercula_EN-CA9420779261_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.Fratercula_EN-CA9420779261_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Flap, dive, survive","Title":"Atlantic puffins, Wales","Copyright":"© FLPA/Alamy","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/51.797381,-5.332342/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-CA&od=2&shading=flat&pp=51.797381,-5.332342;S9;Wales&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260512_Fratercula\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Atlantic+puffin&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260512_0400\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260512_Fratercula"},"Ssd":"20260512","Name":"Fratercula","Market":"EN-CA","Hash":"9420779261","FullDateString":"May 12, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"One of the world's greatest natural wonders stretches through the turquoise waters of the Coral Sea off Australia's northeast shoreline. The Great Barrier Reef, running along the coast of Queensland, is the world's largest coral reef system. It is made up of nearly 3,000 individual reefs and hundreds of islands, spanning more than 2,253 kilometres.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.QueenslandReef_EN-CA9209676432_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.QueenslandReef_EN-CA9209676432_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Underwater architecture","Title":"Great Barrier Reef from above, Queensland, Australia","Copyright":"© Francesco Riccardo Iacomino/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/-18.2871,147.6992/3?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-CA&od=2&shading=flat&pp=-18.2871,147.6992;S9;Great Barrier Reef, Queensland, Australia&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260511_QueenslandReef\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Great+Barrier+Reef+Australia&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260511_0400\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260511_QueenslandReef"},"Ssd":"20260511","Name":"QueenslandReef","Market":"EN-CA","Hash":"9209676432","FullDateString":"May 11, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"On Mother's Day, we honour the care, patience and protection that shape lives everywhere. In the wild, these qualities often stand out most where survival is hardest. Captured in Wapusk National Park in northern Manitoba, today's image shows a polar bear mother and her cubs sharing a playful moment on the Arctic tundra.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.MotherCub_EN-CA9121944440_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.MotherCub_EN-CA9121944440_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"A bond that endures","Title":"Polar bear mother and cubs playing in Wapusk National Park, Manitoba","Copyright":"© Hao Jiang/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"In elephant herds, if a calf loses its mother, other females may adopt it, helping ensure it survives.","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260510_MotherCub\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Mothers+Day&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260510_0400\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260510_MotherCub"},"Ssd":"20260510","Name":"MotherCub","Market":"EN-CA","Hash":"9121944440","FullDateString":"May 10, 2026"}],"LocStrings":{"LOC_HOMEPAGE_VERTICAL_SCROLL_IOTD":"Image of the day","LOC_HOMEPAGE_VERTICAL_SCROLL_IOTD_LEARN_MORE":"Learn more","LOC_HOMEPAGE_VERTICAL_SCROLL_DONATE_NOW":"Donate now","LOC_HOMEPAGE_VERTICAL_SCROLL_FACT":"Quick fact:","LOC_HOMEPAGE_GALLERY_CARD_TITLE":"Recent Homepage images","LOC_HOMEPAGE_VERTICAL_SCROLL_GALLERY_IMAGE_ARIALABEL":"Homepage image for {0}","LOC_HOMEPAGE_ON_THIS_DAY_TITLE":"On this day in history","LOC_HOMEPAGE_ON_THIS_DAY_IMAGE_ARIALABEL":"On this day in {0}, {1}","LOC_HOMEPAGE_SHARE_TOOLTIP":"Share today's Bing homepage","LOC_HOMEPAGE_WALLPAPERDOWNLOAD_TOOLTIP":"Download this image. Use of this image is restricted to wallpaper only.","LOC_MUSCARD_DOWNLOAD_LINK":"Download this image","LOC_HOMEPAGE_WALLPAPERNOTAVAILABLE":"This image is not available 